EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 272300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING FRONTAL TROUGHS WILL EXTEND N THROUGH THE EERN N
SEA WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE OVER EERN PARTS OF THE BRITISH ISLES
AND LOW PRESSURE TO THE N OF THE CULLERCOATS AREA. DURING THURSDAY THE RIDGE
WILL EXTEND FURTHER E AND NE INTO THE AREA BUT WITH A MORE CYCLONIC FLOW
PERSISTING IN THE FAR E. THE RIDGE THEN EXP TO TRANSFER SE ON FRIDAY AS FRONTAL
TROUGHS MOV E INTO THE NW OF THE AREA. CURRENT INDICATIONS ARE THEN FOR FRONTAL
TROUGHS TO MOV SE INTO THE N SEA ON SATURDAY WITH A RIDGE FLW TO THE NW OF
THE CULLERCOATS AREA. NO GALES ARE FCST DURING THIS PERIOD BUT WINDS LIKELY
TO BECOME STRG AT TIMES IN THE NW ON FRIDAY EVENING THESE THEN CURRENTLY
EXP TO TRANSFER E ACROSS NERN PARTS AND MOD ON SATURDAY MORNING
